          <avActivityHighlights>Wind slabs and wet snow represent the main danger.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>In the vicinity of peaks a generally favourable avalanche situation will be encountered in some localities. As the day progresses as a consequence of warming during the day there will be an increase in the danger of wet avalanches. Above approximately 1500 m small small avalanches are possible.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>As a consequence of warming, the likelihood of wet snow slides and avalanches being released will increase in all aspects in all altitude zones.</snowpackStructureComment>
